 UK stocks to watch on Friday are:

 


 BP (BP.L)

 BP may not need a relief well to drill into the bottom of its ruptured Gulf
of Mexico well if a test shows that cement poured in from the top last week
killed the leak, the top official overseeing the spill response said on
Thursday. [ID:nN12108187]

 Also, BP has agreed to pay a record $50.6 million fine for safety violations
at its troubled Texas City, Texas, refinery, U.S. Labor Secretary Hilda Solis
said Thursday. [ID:nWEN8777]

 GLAXOSMITHKLINE (GSK)L&gt;

 GlaxoSmithKline's anti-seizure drug Lamictal can cause a brain inflammation
known as aseptic meningitis, U.S. health regulators said on Thursday.
[ID:nN12110009]

 BARCLAYS (BARC.L)

 The bank's small business arm has refused to sign up to UK lending targets
because it could encourage irresponsible lending, the head of the division told
the Financial Times on Friday. [ID:nLDE67C008]

 


 CAIRN ENERGY (CNE.L)

 Cairn India's (CAIL.BO) oilfield in the desert state of Rajasthan has the
potential to pump 240,000 barrels per day, about twice the current rate, the
company's head, Rahul Dhir, told reporters on Friday. [ID:nDEB003353]

 


 IMAGINATION TECHNOLOGIES IMGT.L

 The chipmaker holds its annual general meeting.

 


    


